Serves: 1Difficulty: EasyIngredients:IceHalf a fresh granadilla1 tot gin1 tsp simple syrupStem of mint leavesTonic waterGin & peach coolerMethod:1) Place the ice in a tumbler.2) Scoop the granadilla pulp out into the glass.3) Pour in the gin and the syrup.4) Top with the tonic water.5) Add the mint, give the cocktail a quick stir and serve.WATCH: How to make a gin and granadilla cocktail, step-by-stepGin, mint and granadilla cocktail.Gin, mint and granadilla cocktail. FULL RECIPE: http://ow.ly/10r6F9 Posted by Sunday Times Food Weekly on Friday, 8 April 2016Gin, mint and granadilla cocktail. FULL RECIPE: http://ow.ly/10r6F9